OL,3,CSewage system needs #52 million
OL,4,Cupgrade for new homes to be built
OL,6,FMore housing cannot be built in unless
OL,7,Fthe island's ageing is upgraded,
OL,8,Faccording to the island's Environment,
OL,9,FHousing and Infrastructure Scrutiny
OL,10,FPanel.
OL,12,FTheir review says #52.4 million must
OL,13,Fbe spent if is to meet its target of
OL,14,Fbuilding 800 new houses a year until
OL,15,F2030, including 3,000 affordable homes.
OL,17,FThe Panel says that Jersey's out-of-
OL,18,Fdate sewage and drainage system is
OL,19,F"holding up" those plans and poses a
OL,20,Fsignificant risk of flooding.
